me internal debate when I was in my low 20's.  At that level your spells are detuned druid spells that don't seem to work very well. At 22 Panic animal was somewhat of a disappointment, it fizzled alot and didn't last long, but as I grew in levels it became alot more reliable. Root was the same way, the only really good utility spell I had was snare. But even so, I was a reasonably good tank, had great taunt, and a few good buffs.  <br>
<br>
Things definately picked up at 30 with sow, and a generally better feel for playing a ranger.  At forty in the outdoors I am a pulling and tanking machine.  With harmony, root, snare, careless lightning, and SoW I can find any mob, harmony, single pull, root any adds and bring a clean pull to my group. I can easily taunt mobs off of healers, casters, and rogues.<br>
<br>
  In highly competitive zones like Everfrost (mammoths), and Rathe Mountains (giants), a ranger can beat most other classes to wandering mobs, tag with an arrow at full sprint, and then tank the monster when back at the group. Then dual weild, double attack, kick, and nuke. Your like an armored food processor.<br>
<br>
When you just don't feel like looking for a group, you can go out on your own and kill with great efficiency. We can be a very independant class if we want.  We can also hunt in high risk areas because with /tracksort distance you'll always know when a big bad player killing beast is nearby. And with snare, and sow you can always tuck your tail between your legs and head for the zone line.<br>
<br>
We can camo to get into places other classes need help with. At first camo is pretty sketchy, but i've found it's fairly reliable at my current level. I'd say it drops early 10% of the time. In your 30's camo and sow are indespensable. Any time I'm traveling through the Great Divide, Eastern Wastes, Kael Drakkal, or other zones with agressive mobs, SoW and Camo make for smooth sailing. Groups also benefit from your ability to SoW.<br>
<br>
I feel like I could go on, but I don't want to inadvertantly attract the nerf bat.<br>
<br>
In a nutshell I love playing a ranger.<br>
<br>
-Traxxus<br>
